1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact subsection 2 of section 43-37-02 and section 43-37-04
2 of the North Dakota Century Code, relating to licensure requirements of a speech-language
3 pathology licensed assistant and temporary licensure.
4 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
5 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Subsection 2 of section 43-37-02 of the North Dakota Century
6 Code is amended and reenacted as follows:
7 2. "Audiology" means the application of principles, methods, and procedures of
8 measurement, testing, evaluation, prediction, consultation, counseling, instruction,
9 habilitation, or rehabilitation related to hearing and disorders of hearing including
10 vestibular testing, for the purpose of evaluating, identifying, managing, preventing,
11 ameliorating, or modifying such disorders and conditions in individuals or groups of
12 individuals.
13 SECTION 2. AMENDMENT. Section 43-37-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is
14 amended and reenacted as follows:
15 43-37-04. Eligibility for licensure.
16 To be eligible for licensure by the board as an audiologist, speech-language pathologist, or
17 speech-language pathology assistant, an applicant shall meet all the following requirements:
18 1. Be of good moral character.
19 2. Possess an appropriate degree from an educational institution recognized by the
20 board.
21 a. An applicant for a speech-language pathologist license must possess at least a
22 master's degree in speech-language pathology.
